msgid "This preference is a binary setting which controls whether or not the library staff can override the circulation and fines rules as they pertain to the placement of holds. Setting this value to \"Don't allow\" will prevent anyone from overriding, setting it to \"Allow\" will allow it. This setting is important because it determines how strict the libraries rules for placing holds are. If this is set to \"Allow\", exceptions can be made for patrons who are otherwise normally in good standing with the library, but there is opportunity for the staff to abuse this function. If it is set to \"Don't allow\", no abuse of the system is possible, but it makes the system entirely inflexible in respect to holds."
